website_summaries.verdict: This large knife set comes with an assortment of harder-to-find blades, including 2 chef knives, a cleaver, a boning knife, and a bird's beak paring knife.
pros: Includes Santoku knife, 8" and 6" chef knives, carving knife, cleaver, bird's beak paring knife, utility knife, 3-1/2" paring knife, bread knife, boning knife, 8 steak knives, fork, scissors, sharpening steel, and rubberwood block
Stainless steel blades with thermoplastic handles
cons: Dishwasher safe, but manufacturer recommends hand washing
Rust relatively quickly if put in dishwasher or not dried after hand-washing

customer_reviews.title: you get what you pay for better options out there
customer_reviews.text: bought this set and after 4 months the scissor handle broke - Contacted Oster (Gibson) and was told that I was could return to retailer (out of Amazon return period) or pay for shipping back to Oster for their review. Needless to say not happy about this for something with supposed lifetime warranty. Cost to ship back to Oster is equivalent to buying new decent pair if culinary scissors. Would take weeks to get replacement presumably the same junk so just ordered new ones as we use often makes us wonder on the quality of the knives in the set, Won't be considering Oster products in the future
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: They are great quality and none have rusted
customer_reviews.text: Bought this set for my mom for Christmas 2015. She loves em! They are great quality and none have rusted!!
customer_reviews.author: Pam W.

customer_reviews.title: Quality for a great price.
customer_reviews.text: My husband opened this knife set and was very impressed with the overall quality and selection. When he asked how much they cost he didn't believe me and then asked if they were on sale. He washed them and started using them right away to prepare dinner and said he was very pleased in how sharp they were and were a good shape. He is very particular about his tools so I know I made the right decision on this purchase.
customer_reviews.author: Plano, TX

customer_reviews.title: Great knife set for everyday use - I'm no chef ...
customer_reviews.text: Great knife set for everyday use - I'm no chef and this is not a pro set - but for everyday kitchen use its great - the storage block is solid wood - comes with sharpener stick - I run everything thru my dishwasher with 3 children at home and steel is good has not rusted or tarnished. For the price the quality is surprising.
customer_reviews.author: Christopher D Hardt

customer_reviews.title: You Get What You Pay For!
customer_reviews.text: Honestly, for this price I don't know how so many of these reviews really expected them to be actually dishwasher safe. I have not put them in the dishwasher and have had no issues with rust. I doesn't take that much to hand clean a nice. I also don't submerge them in water. I like how many I got, and the block for the value. The block even spins. They are not the sharpest knifes and I haven't used the sharpener yet. But if you don't expect a high quality knife set for a low price and you'll be happy with this product!
customer_reviews.author: Bethanie O'Brien

customer_reviews.title: Set Not Like Picture / Appropriately Priced for Quality
customer_reviews.text: Actual set doesn't look like picture. The knives are silver and the holder is black. The quality of the knives (weight) is not great. Decent set for the price, but the picture was deceiving.

customer_reviews.title: So far so good. I haven't used each knife yet
customer_reviews.text: So far so good. I haven't used each knife yet, but of the ones I have used they work well. Seems to hold up fine even through the dishwasher. I love that the block swivels. I have it at the end of my counter and I can turn it to face me no matter which side of the counter I'm on.
customer_reviews.author: afd33

customer_reviews.title: This is a great knife block for a fair price
customer_reviews.text: This is a great knife block for a fair price. I haven't owned them long enough to vouch for the longevity of the blade sharpness, but I usually sharpen my knives before each use anyway. This product is a strong competitor in the consumer-end knife market. I'm not some famous chef, so I don't feel the need to purchase crazy-expensive knives for my home kitchen. These are perfect for me.

customer_reviews.title: Great Deal
customer_reviews.text: So far so good. I replaced this set with a different brand that rusted on the first use. Praying this brand won't rust, discolor or fall apart. This set with so many pieces, such a good price, I am hoping it is going to last! But so far it is perfect.

customer_reviews.title: Great addition to the kitchen

customer_reviews.title: Not the Quality I Expected

We run our dishwasher at night and there were rust spots on the knives by morning.

customer_reviews.title: Gave as a gift, ordering one for myself
customer_reviews.text: purchased this as a gift for my girlfriend. She had one dull knife for everything. There was an extra steak knife in the bok, but that is not a bad thing. Very sharp, well balanced. I am probably ordering another for myself. Update: Purchased a set for myself, and love them. Used the cleaver for the first time today to break down a chicken, made it effortless! Sent my mom a set for Christmas, after spending a week there and doing a bunch of cooking, she had 3 knives, and loves this set too. Order a quality sharpener with them, all but the serated blades can be easily sharpened when needed, but they are holding a good edge.
